==English==

===Etymology===
Compare '''1769''', Oxford Standard text, ''[[s:Bible (King James)|King James Bible]]'', ''[[s:Bible (King James)/Matthew|Matthew]]'', xxiii, 4 — ''For they bind heavy burdens and grievous to be borne, and lay them on men's shoulders; but they themselves will not move them with one of their fingers.''

===Alternative forms===
* [[raise a finger]]

===Verb===
{{en-verb|*}}

# {{lb|en|figuratively|chiefly in the negative}} To make [[minimal]] [[effort]]; to help as little as possible.
#: ''She lets me do all the work and never '''lifts a finger''' to help.''
#* '''1973''', ''Kenya National Assembly Official Record (Hansard): June 12 - July 27'', [http://books.google.com/books?id=ZSdeoZJ2lyUC&pg=PA903&dq=%22lifts+a+finger%22&hl=en&ei=Cmn4TdnXJ4e6vwPzjPWCDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=7&ved=0CEQQ6AEwBjgK#v=onepage&q=%22lifts%20a%20finger%22&f=false page 904],
#*: They weep when they see the country being so much exploited and yet nobody '''lifts a finger'''.
#* {{quote-book|en|title=Little men: novellas and stories‎|page=6|author=Gerald Shapiro|year=2004|passage=You've known about it all along, you haven't '''lifted a finger''', so don't come crying to me. I don't have time for it.}}
#* '''2005''', Larry T. McGehee, B. J. Hutto, ''Southern Seen: Meditations on Past and Present'', [http://books.google.com/books?id=KIeSR5uyT-oC&pg=PA80&dq=%22lifting+a+finger%22&hl=en&ei=gmT4TcveJIukugOKveCDDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=3&ved=0CDQQ6AEwAjgK#v=onepage&q=%22lifting%20a%20finger%22&f=false page 80],
#*: Lifting a finger to greet is dangerous because it may make us feel guilty about not '''lifting a finger''' to help.
# {{&lit|en|lift|finger}}
#* '''2010''', Katharine Rapoport, ''[http://books.google.com/books?id=Htf9e9fFvJQC&pg=PT74&dq=%22lifting+a+finger%22&hl=en&ei=gmT4TcveJIukugOKveCDDA&sa=X&oi=book_result&ct=result&resnum=5&ved=0CD8Q6AEwBDgK#v=onepage&q=%22lifting%20a%20finger%22&f=false Violin For Dummies]'',
#*: So if your next note involves '''''lifting'' a finger''', you need to plan to lift the finger promptly to above its spot on the string so that it's ready to play again at any time.

====Usage notes====
* Most often used in the negative.

